# Flag session

Live tmux sessions can carry a persistent manual flag in `@sesh.flag`. A
flagged session should show an alert-like pip with distinct colour and offer an
`unflag` shortcut in the header.

    :bins jj tmux cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'tmux', and 'cat' are available.

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s alpha "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s beta "cat" (success)
    :t set-option -t beta @sesh.flag 1 (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 100 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

Filter to the pre-flagged session. The header should offer `unflag`, and the
linked SVG snapshot should show the pip in the flag colour rather than the alert
colour.

    :k beta
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: beta
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] unflag
▌⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](flag-session.md.snap.1.light.svg)
![dark](flag-session.md.snap.1.dark.svg)

Pressing `C-f` should clear the persisted tmux option and update the header to
offer `flag` again.

    :k C-f
    :settle -d 2s (settled)
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: beta
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag
▌⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](flag-session.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](flag-session.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

    :t display-message -p -t beta '#{@sesh.flag}' (success)

Pressing `C-f` again should set the persisted tmux option back to `1`.

    :k C-f
    :settle -d 2s (settled)
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: beta
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] unflag
▌⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

![light](flag-session.md.snap.3.light.svg)
![dark](flag-session.md.snap.3.dark.svg)

    :t display-message -p -t beta '#{@sesh.flag}' (success)

```
1
```

